<subSubSection id="129AC9CB16ADC8BA76B0ACAB3C77B1A2" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" type="type species">
<paragraph id="1826514A2C1420046B1D12A6EE401DAE" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A6BD682EB53A752DE59F37DB8DF7EFF5" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName id="8D8F7E4BE48113EB536A4B1F6B79DE79" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helix (Chloritis) pseudomiara" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pseudomiara" subGenus="Chloritis">Helix (Chloritis) pseudomiara</taxonomicName>
Bavay &amp; Dautzenberg, 1909 by monotypy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1FD3941AEE6746659902E02701EF25D4" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">
The anatomically-examined specimen (i.e., on which the genus is based) was in fact 
<taxonomicName id="4F0018EB1D5E7EC6A674A34533E811B3" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helix condoriana" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="condoriana">
<emphasis id="46DDE06D38601889793DEA7CE1ED4404" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">Helix condoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Under the provisions of Article 70.3 ICZN, we herewith replace the original type species 
<taxonomicName id="D30884ADDD1D113DD295DA3E63AF741C" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helix (Chloritis) pseudomiara" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pseudomiara" subGenus="Chloritis">Helix (Chloritis) pseudomiara</taxonomicName>
Bavay &amp; Dautzenberg, 1909 with 
<taxonomicName id="8F30298ADE37AC82E953167DA8A897D6" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helix condoriana" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="condoriana">
<emphasis id="992D8560B923413C2266C1A824CBE09A" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">Helix condoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Crosse &amp; Fischer, 1863 as the type species of 
<taxonomicName id="3E4C1EF7F39FD50B917230BCCFF25E6F" class="Gastropoda" family="Camaenidae" genus="Bellatrachia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bellatrachia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="382E254E1496774208A5223C7E3A91E9" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">Bellatrachia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schileyko, 2018 to serve the stability of nomenclature.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9F367A063AA7A60D98E315D5CE80613B" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" type="included species">
<paragraph id="2B8A677855FEE3A55DAFB2C237A1AF98" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">Included species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="22077701A77F8AD7B01E1DF76D7BB629" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName id="C3E69505264877560BE0F0B1037D181E" class="Gastropoda" family="Camaenidae" genus="Bellatrachia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bellatrachia condoriana" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="condoriana">
<emphasis id="1CCCC3C002E938DE9AC7154063123605" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">Bellatrachia condoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Crosse &amp; Fischer, 1863).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D1F9EDDDF12AE34AC9DDEC885ABB7D13" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="54C142F1398180E401E1E3F04B44CA8A" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9F6392DB23DBA7A9D20928037C5CB96" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">
Shell depressed globular, apex not sunken, hairs or hair scars cover the entire shell. Penis rather long, subcylindrical, its inner surface bears longitudinal pilasters; penial verge absent; penial caecum absent; epiphallus slender, long, convoluted; retractor muscle attached at the penis-epiphallus transition; flagellum thick, with attenuated tip, approximately 2-2.5 times shorter than epiphallus; vagina slender, shorter than penis; stalk of bursa copulatrix long, with thickening at some distance from its origin, shape of bursa unknown (based on 
<bibRefCitation id="A3D829CBB15D5646A6BD107CC71EC620" author="Schileyko, A" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica" pageId="12" pageNumber="149" pagination="169 - 174" refId="B22" refString="Schileyko, A, 2018. On the genus Trachia auct. (Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Camaenidae). . Ruthenica 28: 169 - 174" title="On the genus Trachia auct. (Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Camaenidae)." volume="28" year="2018">Schileyko 2018</bibRefCitation>
; see 
<figureCitation id="7FFAD67BE6043B646CD0A37547983BDE" captionStart="Figures 3â€“4" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3 - 4. Original specimen &quot; Bellatrachia pseudomiara &quot; sensu Schileyko 3 shell (Schileyko 2018: 170, Fig. 1), D = 23.2 mm, A. Sysoev, photograph x 2 4 Morphology of the genital organs of &quot; Bellatrachia pseudomiara &quot; sensu Schileyko (2018), modified after Schileyko (2018)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.865.36296.figures3-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/319420" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="00D968D6F6E6FD8A847D0D76FB8DAB01" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" type="description">
